00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:43.390
to the book and we're
going to send her a copy

00:17:43.390 --> 00:17:45.040
because when I explained to her.

00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:46.340
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson : I just
presented her with a copy.

00:17:46.340 --> 00:17:47.640
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden:
You presented her.

00:17:47.640 --> 00:17:48.940
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson: I did.

00:17:48.940 --> 00:17:51.260
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: Yes because
she was so intrigued growing up,

00:17:51.260 --> 00:17:54.770
being Puerto Rican and when
I told her about this book

00:17:54.770 --> 00:17:59.510
and the way it celebrates
when you begin

00:17:59.510 --> 00:18:02.570
to celebrate being different.

00:18:02.570 --> 00:18:06.950
It took me a lot longer and I
wish I had a book like this.

00:18:06.950 --> 00:18:08.250
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson:
Thank you,

00:18:08.250 --> 00:18:09.550
so I should read part of it?

00:18:09.550 --> 00:18:10.890
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: I
think you should.

00:18:10.890 --> 00:18:12.790
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson: Okay.

00:18:12.790 --> 00:18:16.130
&gt;&gt; Read all of it.

00:18:16.130 --> 00:18:19.370
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson: I don't
think we have time to read all

00:18:19.370 --> 00:18:21.460
of it but I can definitely read.

00:18:21.460 --> 00:18:23.810
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: The good parts.

00:18:23.810 --> 00:18:25.970
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson:
The day you began.

00:18:25.970 --> 00:18:28.600
There will be times when
you walk into a room

00:18:28.600 --> 00:18:31.030
and no one there
is quite like you.

00:18:31.030 --> 00:18:34.830
Maybe it will be your
skin, your clothes

00:18:34.830 --> 00:18:36.880
or the curl of your hair.

00:18:36.880 --> 00:18:41.640
There will be times when no one
understands the way words curl

00:18:41.640 --> 00:18:42.940
from your mouth.

00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:46.190
The beautiful language of
the country you left behind.

00:18:46.190 --> 00:18:47.680
My name is Ricaberto
[assumed spelling],

00:18:47.680 --> 00:18:49.180
we just moved her
from Venezuela.

00:18:49.180 --> 00:18:52.720
And because they don't
understand the class will fill

00:18:52.720 --> 00:18:56.450
with laughter until the
teacher quiets everyone.

00:18:56.450 --> 00:19:00.630
Ricaberto from Venezuela,
your teacher says so softly

00:19:00.630 --> 00:19:03.370
and beautifully that your
name and homelands sound

00:19:03.370 --> 00:19:07.150
like flowers blooming, the
first bright notes of a song.

00:19:08.340 --> 00:19:10.790
There will be time when
the words don't come,

00:19:10.790 --> 00:19:14.030
your own voice once
huge now smaller

00:19:14.030 --> 00:19:16.660
when the teacher asks what
did you do last summer.

00:19:16.660 --> 00:19:18.830
Tell the class your story.

00:19:18.830 --> 00:19:21.690
We went to France Chalay
[assumed spelling] says.

00:19:21.690 --> 00:19:24.810
These shells came
from a beach in Maine.

00:19:24.810 --> 00:19:28.240
A boy named Jonathan holds out
a jar filled with tiny shells

00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:31.130
so fragile they look
like they'll turn to dust

00:19:31.130 --> 00:19:33.860
in your own untraveled hands.

00:19:33.860 --> 00:19:36.360
My whole family went
to India, Spain,

00:19:36.360 --> 00:19:40.900
South Carolina each souvenir
a small triumph of a journey

00:19:40.900 --> 00:19:44.360
that travels going on and on.

00:19:44.360 --> 00:19:45.660
And as you stand at that,

00:19:45.660 --> 00:19:49.610
in front of that room you can
only remember how the heat waved

00:19:49.610 --> 00:19:51.420
as it lifted off the curb.

00:19:51.420 --> 00:19:54.750
And your days spent at home
caring for your little sister

00:19:54.750 --> 00:19:58.740
who made you laugh out loud and
hugged you hard at nap time.

00:19:58.740 --> 00:20:01.280
You can only remember the
books you kept on reading long

00:20:01.280 --> 00:20:03.050
after she had fallen to sleep.

00:20:03.050 --> 00:20:06.650
And in that room where no
one else is quite like you,

00:20:06.650 --> 00:20:09.060
you'll look down at
your own empty hands

00:20:09.060 --> 00:20:13.770
and wonder what good is this
when other students were flying

00:20:13.770 --> 00:20:17.280
and sailing and going somewhere.

00:20:17.280 --> 00:20:20.140
There will be times when
the lunch your mother packed

00:20:20.140 --> 00:20:22.940
for you is to strange
or to unfamiliar

00:20:22.940 --> 00:20:25.530
for others to love as you do.

00:20:25.530 --> 00:20:28.060
When even your own friend
Naja will wrinkle her nose

00:20:28.060 --> 00:20:30.660
and say what is there,
what's in there anyway.

00:20:30.660 --> 00:20:33.680
And you'll wonder how she
doesn't see the rice beneath the

00:20:33.680 --> 00:20:34.980
meat and [foreign word].

00:20:34.980 --> 00:20:36.280
You'll wonder why
she doesn't remember

00:20:36.280 --> 00:20:40.070
that rice is the most
popular food in the world.

00:20:40.070 --> 00:20:43.060
There will be times when the
climbing bars are too high,

00:20:43.060 --> 00:20:45.070
the run is to fast and far,

00:20:45.070 --> 00:20:48.220
the game isn't one you
can really ever play.

00:20:48.220 --> 00:20:50.600
I don't want them on
our team, you can watch,

00:20:50.600 --> 00:20:53.200
maybe you can have a turn later.

00:20:53.200 --> 00:20:55.140
There will be times
when the world feels

00:20:55.140 --> 00:20:58.660
like a place your standing
all the way outside of.

00:20:58.660 --> 00:21:02.150
And all that stands beside
you is your own brave self,

00:21:02.150 --> 00:21:05.510
steady as steel and ready,
even though you don't

00:21:05.510 --> 00:21:07.490
yet know what you're ready for.

00:21:07.490 --> 00:21:11.440
There will be times when
you walk into a room

00:21:11.440 --> 00:21:15.430
and no one there is quite like
you until the day you begin

00:21:15.430 --> 00:21:17.230
to share your stories.

00:21:17.230 --> 00:21:19.310
My name is Angelina and
I spent my whole summer

00:21:19.310 --> 00:21:21.510
with my little sister
you tell the class.

00:21:21.510 --> 00:21:24.220
Your voice stronger than
it was a minute ago.

00:21:24.220 --> 00:21:25.790
Reading books and
telling stories

00:21:25.790 --> 00:21:27.330
and even though we were
right on our block it was

00:21:27.330 --> 00:21:30.450
like we got to go everywhere.

00:21:30.450 --> 00:21:33.450
Your name is like my
sisters, Ricaberto says,

00:21:33.450 --> 00:21:35.260
her name is Angelina too.

00:21:35.260 --> 00:21:38.210
And all at once in the room
where no one else is quite

00:21:38.210 --> 00:21:42.140
like you, the world opens
itself up a little wider.

00:21:42.140 --> 00:21:44.620
To make some space for you.

00:21:44.620 --> 00:21:46.350
This is the day you begin

00:21:46.350 --> 00:21:49.580
to find the places inside your
laughter and your lunches,

00:21:49.580 --> 00:21:51.910
your books, your
travel and your stories,

00:21:51.910 --> 00:21:55.070
where every new friend has
something a little like you.

00:21:55.070 --> 00:21:58.270
And something else
so fabulously,

00:21:58.270 --> 00:22:01.510
not quite like you, at all.

