00:22:15.640 --> 00:22:17.710
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson:
I read the whole thing.

00:22:17.710 --> 00:22:19.010
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:22:19.010 --> 00:22:20.310
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: Thank you.

00:22:20.310 --> 00:22:26.410
Because when you thought about
this what were you trying to do?

00:22:26.410 --> 00:22:28.510
Give that strength?

00:22:28.510 --> 00:22:31.570
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson: I
was, the book was inspired

00:22:31.570 --> 00:22:34.120
by a passage from Brown
Girl Dreaming where I talk

00:22:34.120 --> 00:22:35.580
about my great great grandfather

00:22:35.580 --> 00:22:39.080
who is the only black
kid in his class in Ohio.

00:22:39.080 --> 00:22:47.360
In the 1920's and 30's and
growing up my mom always said

00:22:47.360 --> 00:22:50.070
to us, you know they'll be
times when you walk into a room

00:22:50.070 --> 00:22:51.370
where no one is like you.

00:22:51.370 --> 00:22:54.380
And deal with it, like
what are you going to do.

00:22:54.380 --> 00:22:56.430
And don't be afraid of it.

00:22:56.430 --> 00:23:00.360
And I think especially in
our country at this moment

00:23:00.360 --> 00:23:03.290
in time there's a lot of fear.

00:23:03.290 --> 00:23:06.720
And I think there are a lot
of people walking into rooms,

00:23:06.720 --> 00:23:09.150
young and old who
don't have a sense

00:23:09.150 --> 00:23:11.010
that they belong in that space.

00:23:11.010 --> 00:23:14.080
Or that they have a
right to that space.

00:23:14.080 --> 00:23:19.120
Or that everyone else in that
space has something in common

00:23:19.120 --> 00:23:21.700
with each other and
they're outside of that.

00:23:21.700 --> 00:23:26.950
And so I started writing The
Day You Begin to explore that

00:23:26.950 --> 00:23:31.350
and understand for myself first
because I always write books

00:23:31.350 --> 00:23:33.440
so I can have a better
understanding.

00:23:33.440 --> 00:23:39.260
And then a sense of empowerment
that, that every time we walk

00:23:39.260 --> 00:23:42.430
into a room we're a
gift to that room right?

00:23:42.430 --> 00:23:47.310
You know and the room should
be happy to have us in it.

00:23:47.310 --> 00:23:54.090
So, so The Day You
Begin began from there.

00:23:54.090 --> 00:23:55.590
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: Well
you are a gift to us.

00:23:55.590 --> 00:23:57.590
&gt;&gt; Jacqueline Woodson: Oh
so you are you Dr. Hayden.

